===Etymology 1===
* First attested in the late 14th century. From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|abstinent|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|abstinēns}}, present participle of {{m|la|abstineō}}.
* See [[abstain]]

====Adjective====
{{en-adj}}

# [[refraining|Refraining]] from [[indulgence]], especially from the indulgence of appetite; [[abstemious]]; [[continent]]; [[temperate]]. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=10}}</ref>
#: {{rfquotek|Beaumont and Fletcher}}

